40|$|This thesis mainly {{deals with}} the {{analysis}} of the substantive aspects of criminal liability and sanctioning of legal entities within the meaning of the Act No. 418 / 2011 Coll., on criminal liability of <b>legal</b> <b>persons</b> and proceedings against them (hereinafter "ZTOPO"), entered into force on January 1, 2012 in the Czech Republic. The law governing the criminal liability of <b>legal</b> <b>persons</b> is effective for almost five years, yet this topic is still very controversial and debated. The aim {{of this study is to}} provide a comprehensive brief overview the issue of criminal liability and sanctioning of <b>legal</b> <b>persons</b> in the Czech Republic. The third chapter, which {{deals with the}} substantive provisions of ZTOPO regarding the criminal liability of <b>legal</b> <b>persons,</b> is the main content of this work and then also the fourth chapter, which is devoted to the question of delimitation of sanctions, that can be imposed to condemned <b>legal</b> <b>person.</b> This work deals with legal regulation of legal entities, comparisons of the criminal liability legislation of legal entities in France, the Slovak Republic and in Germany, the development of criminal liability of <b>legal</b> <b>persons</b> in the Czech Republic and in particular analysis of selected substantive provisions of ZTOPO. It is also pointed out some of the major shortcomings of the [...] ...|$|R
